Elton John, whose real name is Reginald Dwight, is one of the most successful musicians of the 20th century, selling over 250 million records. This vinyl live album was released in 1978, and features five songs recorded at London’s Royal Festival Hall and five songs from a concert in Madison Square Garden in New York.

“Carry On Collecting” is a project set up by the Museum of Hartlepool to collect objects which represent everyday life in the town and beyond, from the 1950s through to the present day. The collection also attempts to represent the diversity of the people of Hartlepool over the past 60 years.
